# Engineering harness (this repo)

This repo vendors the AIOS engineering harness at `.harness/`. Two contracts govern all work:

- **`AGENTS.md`** (repo root) — slow-changing operational facts and the error ledger.
- **`CONSTITUTION.md`** (repo root) — the pinned engineering principles (spec-before-code,
  verification-is-the-value, the autonomy ladder, mandatory compounding, the simplification bar).

Read both before non-trivial work. The available skills live in `.harness/skills/*/SKILL.md`
(plan-first, tdd-fail-first, systematic-debugging, verify-change, code-review, simplify-pass,
compound-learnings, …) — read the matching `SKILL.md` in full before doing that kind of work.

Enforcement is not advisory: `.cursor/hooks.json` runs the harness guards (secrets, protected
paths, destructive commands, **worktree discipline**) before edits/commands and the verification
gate (`.harness/check`) at stop. Do feature work in a dedicated `git worktree`, never on a branch
committed in the primary checkout.
